The annual Kenya Bankers Association chairman's ball was held at the Radisson Blu Hotel on Thursday evening.Now its in second edition, the event saw the attendance of several financial institutions including Standard Chartered CEO for Kenya and East Africa Lamin Manjang, NIC bank chief executive John Gachora and NSE chief executive Geoffrey Odundo. The guests were treated to entertainment from poet Julie Wang'ombe and H-art The Band.Also present were KBA chief executive Habil Olaka and UK High Commissioner Nic Hailey. A cheque of Sh4 million was presented to the Kenya Community Development Foundation through its executive director Janet Mawiyoo.